High-Confidence Concrete Findings (Most Important)

These are the ones I would actually open issues for immediately:

❌ 1) Silent unauthenticated fallback is still real

Files:

engramia/api/auth.py:79
engramia/api/auth.py:205
engramia/api/auth.py:222
engramia/api/app.py:72-74
docker-compose.yml:24

Problem:
If ENGRAMIA_API_KEYS is empty and DB auth is not active, API can still run effectively without auth.

Impact:
This is exactly the kind of thing that leads to:

“We thought prod was protected, but staging config leaked into prod.”

Fix:
Make this impossible unless:

ENGRAMIA_AUTH_MODE=dev
and
ENGRAMIA_ALLOW_NO_AUTH=true

Anything else should fail startup.

